Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper discusses the comparison of two duplexing techniques in wireless communication networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the impact of duplexing techniques on the throughput of wireless powered communication networks, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the impact of duplexing techniques on the performance of wireless powered communication networks, which is related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the allocation of bandwidth for energy and data transmission, which is related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper discusses the technical aspects of wireless powered communication networks, which may involve hardware architecture.
